COMPETITIVE POSITIONING
Current Market Context:
Renovo competes with local scrap yards (low digital sophistication) and national chains (high digital polish but less personal). The opportunity is "Modern Local"â€”sophisticated digital experience that maintains community trust and fair dealing.
Positioning Statement (Proposed):

"The fair, fast, hassle-free way to turn your scrap metal into cash. Real prices. Real time. Real service."


METRICS TO TRACK (Post-Redesign)

Lead Generation: Form submissions, chat initiations, calls from website
Conversion: Drop-off reservations booked, first-time vs. repeat visitors
Engagement: Time on page (materials), filter interactions, price checks
SEO: Organic traffic to "scrap metal prices," "sell aluminum," location-based terms
Retention: Return visitor rate, review generation, referral sources
Support: Pre-visit calls (should decrease with better pricing transparency)


CONCLUSION
Renovo's website currently serves a compliance + transparency function (appropriate for a regulated business). However, it misses a strategic opportunity to drive growth through better user experience, emotional storytelling, and modern design.
The proposed changes balance:

Avant-garde aesthetics (glassmorphism, bento grids, animated micro-interactions) with functional simplicity (no gimmicks)
Brand heritage (navy + strong logo) with contemporary refresh (emerald accent, refined typography)
Operational transparency (pricing, hours, compliance) with emotional resonance (sustainability narrative, human testimonials)

The result is a website that not only converts better but also positions Renovo as a forward-thinking partner in the circular economyâ€”not just a processor of scrap metal.
Recommendation: Start with Phase 1 (hero redesign, pricing widget, nav restructure) to validate improvements quickly. These changes are low-risk, high-impact, and can be launched within 12 weeks.